<item>
            <title>[JCR-27] ArrayIndexOutofBoundException while setting a reference property</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-27</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>I have a node whith a multivalued reference property.&lt;br/&gt;
I try to add a reference as follows (the spec is outdated at this point, so I&amp;#39;m not sure if I use the right approach to add a reference):&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;ReferenceValue rv = new ReferenceValue(rn.getNode(&amp;quot;pages/mjo:page&amp;quot;));&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Value[] values = {rv};&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;tstN.setProperty(&amp;quot;mjo:testCon&amp;quot;,values);&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;session.save();&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
This results in a &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
2004-12-09 16:11:43,614 WARN org.apache.jackrabbit.core.ItemManager - node at /pages/mjo:page has invalid definitionId (1512950840)&lt;br/&gt;
java.lang.ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException: 0&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.apache.jackrabbit.core.ItemImpl.validateTransientItems(ItemImpl.java:626)&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.apache.jackrabbit.core.ItemImpl.save(ItemImpl.java:1148)&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.apache.jackrabbit.core.SessionImpl.save(SessionImpl.java:633)&lt;br/&gt;
	at de.freaquac.test.JCRTest.main(JCRTest.java:174)&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException is never a good sign, so I assume it&amp;#39;s a bug. I should say that crx throws the same exception if I try it there.&lt;br/&gt;
</description>
